Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.32,0:41:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't end up with a war on this planet either, did she?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.09,0:41:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A little happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.76,0:41:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless her.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.23,0:41:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So Monday morning quarterbacking, you see, it's compassion for the limitations of the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.84,0:41:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The human ego, by its structure, is unable to tell truth from falsehood. The human ego is like the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.34,0:41:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,hardware of a computer. Society then puts in the software, but the hardware can't protect itself
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.75,0:41:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,against whatever is being programmed like a computer. So they're eating the air. So it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.59,0:41:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's being programmed with, you know, Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.94,0:42:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates didn't believe, you know, criticize democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.07,0:42:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates said that the difficulty with democracy is every idiot will not have a vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.23,0:42:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the uninformed, the unintelligent, and those who do not value or know the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.63,0:42:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,will have equal rights with those who do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.57,0:42:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, he believed in oligarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.98,0:42:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And oligarchy is ruled by the few who are picked by virtue of their education,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.63,0:42:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,their wisdom, their integrity, and we'd calibrate their level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.40,0:42:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'd only have the best cooks, the best cooks in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.21,0:42:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, anybody who's persuasive can get in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.21,0:42:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But it takes more than persuasiveness in getting votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.94,0:42:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes a profound integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.71,0:42:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we saw that with President Truman.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.48,0:42:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the terrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.51,0:42:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Terrible problem he had, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.00,0:42:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't envy any of the presidents, but Truman I felt the serious for.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.69,0:43:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he had the problem of triage.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.57,0:43:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to allow six, they estimated seven million people will die if we invade Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.32,0:43:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They will fight to the last man.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.57,0:43:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven million die, or you can pick out a population of 180,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.76,0:43:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,By killing 180,000, you save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.01,0:43:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You save seven million.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.15,0:43:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called triage.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.82,0:43:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Every physician faces this all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.92,0:43:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.92,0:43:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We faced it in the military, World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.48,0:43:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Two guys overboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.61,0:43:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to turn back the ship right out of the middle of the fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.13,0:43:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and pick up these two guys and risk the fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.11,0:43:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.07,0:43:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you've been through war, you don't really understand triage.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.86,0:43:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Or unless you've been in the emergency room of a hospital at midnight on a Saturday night,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.67,0:43:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,where they come in with ice picks in their head.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.61,0:43:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Guy walks in, he's got an ice pick.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.48,0:43:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm on duty on Saturday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.84,0:43:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in New York City, Belleville.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.01,0:44:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a guy with an ice pick in his head, and it's coming out his other eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.98,0:44:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.59,0:44:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Another guy was just in a subway accident, and his brain is squashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.67,0:44:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ER is already full to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.46,0:44:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So which one are you going to let go?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.63,0:44:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You do the ice pick guy, the other brain's going to swell up, hemorrhage, and he'll be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.42,0:44:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do him, the guy with the ice pick will have encephalitis and affected brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.78,0:44:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and so on and so forth by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.61,0:44:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So triage is something the American public...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.75,0:44:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The American public doesn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.88,0:44:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So people who criticize Truman's decision have no heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.76,0:44:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They may come from smart-smart, but they have no heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.67,0:44:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because can you imagine the crushing horror that he went through?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.46,0:44:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I always admired Truman.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.71,0:44:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he ever?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.11,0:44:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, boy, I was a son of a bitch, but I made that decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.38,0:44:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all agonized with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.73,0:45:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think what public officials and presidents and congressmen all need is less criticism
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.71,0:45:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and more support.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.73,0:45:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, you know, we know you've got a hard job.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.42,0:45:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how we all feel.
